# Iconography

Geizhals Icons should be kept simple and neutral. We are using mostly icons from the [Material Design icons](https://material.io/resources/icons/) set. In certain cases it may be required to create custom icons – these should follow the style of Material Design icons.

## Outlined versus filled icons

Use both filled and outlined icons depending the required context. For instance, a filled icon could be used to indicate that something is "on", while an outlined icon could indicate that something is "off".

